Section 1:
1 L.D. 1213
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 AGRICULTURE, CONSERVATION AND FORESTRY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 502, L.D. 1213, “An Act to Allow the
10 Premiums and Gratuities Paid for Any Agricultural Events Approved by the Commissioner
11 of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to Be Considered in Apportionment of Stipends
12 to Agricultural Fairs”
13 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
14 'An Act Regarding Apportionment of Stipends to Agricultural Fairs'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 7 MRSA §81, sub-§10, as enacted by PL 2005, c. 563, §3, is amended to
18 read:
19 10. Premium. "Premium" means a ribbon, trophy or monetary amount or a service or
20 object with monetary value awarded as a prize in a competition or event.
21 Sec. 2. 7 MRSA §85, first ¶, as enacted by PL 2005, c. 563, §3, is amended to read:
22 The Treasurer of State shall establish the Fair Fund and shall annually credit a sum of
23 money equal to 5% of the total amount designated as state share in accordance with Title
24 8, section 286 to the Fair Fund. The commissioner shall make distributions from the Fair
25 Fund only to licensees eligible for a stipend under section 86, subsections 5 and 6.
26 Distributions are prorated according to the amount of premiums and gratuities actually paid
27 by those licensees in full and in cash or valuable equivalent. Restrictions on premiums and
28 gratuities used to determine apportionment of a stipend under section 86, subsection 5
29 apply to distribution from the Fair Fund.
30 Sec. 3. 7 MRSA §86, sub-§5, as enacted by PL 2005, c. 563, §3, is amended to
31 read:
32 5. Distribution to all eligible licensees. The amount remaining in the Stipend Fund
33 after distributions in accordance with subsections 2, 3 and 4 must be divided among fair
34 licensees meeting the eligibility criteria in subsection 6, prorated according to the amount
Page 1 - 132LR1440(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 502, L.D. 1213
315 of premiums and gratuities actually paid by those licensees in full and in cash or valuable
326 equivalent.
3 In determining distribution under this subsection, no an allowance is may not be made on
4 premiums offered and paid by a licensee at any competition or event held other than during
5 the period at in which its annual fair is held. Allowance may not be made or consideration
6 given for lump sums, payments or premiums previously arranged and agreed upon for the
7 presentation and display of any animals or products without regard to competition or event.
8 Premiums and gratuities used to determine apportionment under this subsection are limited
9 to those paid for:
10 A. Livestock and poultry;
11 B. Vegetables, grains, fruits and flowers;
12 C. Products derived from livestock and dairy products;
13 D. Home-canned, home-cooked and home-baked goods;
14 E. Grange and farm exhibits;
15 F. Boys' and girls' club exhibits;
16 F-1. Youth agriculture events;
17 G. Mechanical arts exhibits;
18 H. Domestic and fancy articles Arts and crafts produced in the home;
19 I. Pulling contests for equines and oxen; and
20 J. Pulling contests for farm tractors and pickup trucks.;
21 K. Educational agricultural talks, workshops and demonstrations; and
22 L. Any other agricultural event approved by the commissioner.
23 Sec. 4. 7 MRSA §86, sub-§8, as amended by PL 2021, c. 681, Pt. J, §1, is further
24 amended to read:
25 8. Maximum allowed distribution from Stipend Fund. A licensee may not receive
26 a stipend from the Stipend Fund greater than the amount actually raised and spent by the
27 licensee on premiums and gratuities in the classes provided in subsection 5. A licensee
28 may not receive a stipend from the Stipend Fund in excess of $10,000, except that this
29 limitation does not apply to any additional stipend provided for by Title 8, section 287 or
30 to funds distributed from the Fair Fund in accordance with section 85, the Agricultural Fair
31 Support Fund in accordance with section 91 or the Agricultural Fair Promotion Fund in
32 accordance with section 103.
33 Sec. 5. 7 MRSA §88, sub-§1, ¶B, as enacted by PL 2005, c. 563, §3, is amended
34 to read:
35 B. The commissioner submits a certificate to the executive director of the State
36 Harness Racing Commission stating that the commissioner has examined the claim of
37 the licensee and determined that the licensee has complied with sections 86 and 87 and
38 has awarded and paid as premiums and gratuities a sum equal to or greater than the
39 stipend received by the licensee.'
Page 2 - 132LR1440(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 502, L.D. 1213
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment replaces the bill, changes the title and makes technical changes to the
55 statutes relating to the Stipend Fund and the amount distributed among fair licensees. The
66 amendment specifically adds educational agricultural talks, workshops and demonstrations
77 to the list of competitions and events that may be considered in the calculation of
88 apportionment for stipends; as in the bill, the amendment also specifies that any agricultural
99 event approved by the Commissioner of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry may be
1100 used to determine the apportionment. The amendment removes the obsolete term
1111 "gratuities" from the laws governing agricultural fairs and pulling events.
1122 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1133 (See attached)
Page 3 - 132LR1440(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
